<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1055" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1055">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14726a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Johnson</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You are instructed to deliver a most earnest warning to the commanders of
                            both factions carrying on warfare about Matamoros that they must conduct
                            their operations at Matamoros in such manner as not to menace the lives
                            of American citizens at Brownsville by firing across the border.
                            Telegraph results representations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>